Privacy Policy for Aranest
Last Updated: June 14, 2024
Thank you for choosing Aranest. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information about you when you use our real estate app, Aranest.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information:
When you use Aranest, we may collect personal information that you provide to us, such as:

Name
Email address
Phone number
Address
Payment information (if applicable)
Profile information, including preferences and search history
1.2 Usage Data:
We automatically collect information about your interactions with the app, including:

Device information (e.g., device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers)
Log information (e.g., IP address, access times, and pages viewed)
Location data (if you enable location services)
Usage data (e.g., features used, search queries, and interaction with content)
1.3 Cookies and Tracking Technologies:
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect and use information about your usage of the app and to provide a better user experience.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:

To provide, maintain, and improve the app
To personalize your experience and show you properties and content tailored to your preferences
To communicate with you, including sending updates, notifications, and promotional messages
To process transactions and manage your account
To monitor and analyze usage and trends to improve the app
To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights
3. Sharing Your Information
We may share your information in the following circumstances:

With Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as payment processing, data analysis, and customer support.
With Other Users: When you interact with other users on the app, such as contacting a property seller or landlord, your information may be shared with them.
For Legal Reasons: We may disclose your information if required by law or if we believe it is necessary to protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of others.
In Business Transfers: If we undergo a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
4. Your Choices
4.1 Account Information:
You can update or delete your account information at any time by accessing your account settings. If you wish to delete your account, please contact us at support@aranest.com.

4.2 Marketing Communications:
You can opt-out of receiving promotional emails from us by following the instructions in those emails or by updating your preferences in the app settings.

4.3 Location Data:
You can control the collection of location data through your device settings.

5. Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Children’s Privacy
Aranest is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you by posting the updated policy on the app and updating the “Last Updated” date above. Your continued use of the app after any changes indicates your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:

Aranest
Email: support@aranest.com

By using Aranest, you agree to the collection and use of your information as outlined in this Privacy Policy.
